name: Development release 0.8.9 supporting PHP 7.0 syntax.
body:
The 0.8.x versions will be tracking syntax from PHP versions 7.0.x and are runnable on PHP 7+. Please use a later release of Phan for PHP 7.1 syntax.

See the file [NEWS](https://github.com/phan/phan/blob/0.8.8/NEWS) for what has changed in this version.

name: Development release 0.9.7 supporting PHP 7.1 syntax.
body:
**This is the last 0.9.x release. Users should upgrade to `php-ast` 0.1.5+ and Phan 0.10.x for future releases** 

The 0.9.x and 0.10.x versions will be tracking syntax from PHP versions 7.1.x and are runnable on PHP 7.1+. Please use version 0.8.x if you're using a version of PHP < 7.1.

See the file [NEWS](https://github.com/phan/phan/blob/0.9.7/NEWS) for what has changed in this version.

name: Development release 0.10.0 supporting PHP 7.1 syntax
body:
The 0.10.x versions will be tracking syntax from PHP versions 7.1.x and are runnable on PHP 7.1+.
Please use version 0.8.x if you're using a version of PHP < 7.1.
See the file [NEWS](https://github.com/phan/phan/blob/0.10.0/NEWS) for what has changed in this version.

Phan 0.10.x versions are similar to the corresponding 0.9.x versions, except that they use AST version 50 instead of 40. As a result, Phan 0.10.x requires php-ast 0.1.5+, while 0.9.x requires php-ast 0.1.4+.
If a project uses third party phan plugins, those plugins may need to be upgraded.
Users of Phan 0.9.x versions should upgrade to 0.10.x when possible.

name: Development Release 0.8.7 supporting PHP 7.0 syntax
body:
Future releases (0.8.8+, 0.9.6+, 0.10.0+, etc.) will be published to phan/phan instead of etsy/phan on packagist.

After a few more patch releases, Phan 0.8.x will switch from AST version 40 (requires php-ast 0.1.4+)
to AST version 50 (0.1.5+).


The 0.8.x versions will be tracking syntax from PHP versions 7.0.x and are runnable on PHP 7+. Please use a later release of Phan for PHP 7.1 syntax.

See the file [NEWS](https://github.com/phan/phan/blob/0.8.7/NEWS) for what has changed in this version.

name: Development release 0.9.5 supporting PHP 7.1 syntax
body:
The 0.9.x versions will be tracking syntax from PHP versions 7.1.x and are runnable on PHP 7.1+. Please use version 0.8.x if you're using a version of PHP < 7.1.

See the file [NEWS](https://github.com/phan/phan/blob/0.9.5/NEWS) for what has changed in this version.

---

Future releases (0.8.8+, 0.9.6+, 0.10.0+, etc.) will be published to phan/phan instead of etsy/phan on packagist.

If you are using phan 0.9.x, it's recommended to switch to phan 0.10.y releases
(0.10.x depends on php-ast 0.1.5+ for AST version 50).
Phan 0.9.x will be supported for only a few more patch versions.
(and Phan 0.8.x will switch to AST version 50 after that)

name: Development Release 0.4
body: This release is on a stable code base that we want to get out so that folks don't need to depend on the 0.3 release. The 1.0 release isn't terribly far away.

name: Development Release 0.3
body:
This release is on a fairly stable code base that we want to get out so that folks don't need to depend on the ancient 0.2 release.

Please report any issues at https://github.com/etsy/phan/issues so that we can get a clean 1.0 out.

body: We're creating this release so that we can play nice with package managers (https://github.com/etsy/phan/issues/8).
